<subSubSection pageId="51" pageNumber="52" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="51.[151,1437,326,636]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,502,529]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Distribution.</emphasis>
This species was previously recorded from 
<collectingCountry box="[852,998,503,529]" name="Saudi Arabia" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Saudi Arabia</collectingCountry>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Dawah, H. A. &amp; Abdullah, M. A." box="[1042,1347,503,530]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" pagination="182 - 192" refId="ref27734" refString="Dawah, H. A. &amp; Abdullah, M. A. (2006) New records of Chloropidae (Diptera) from Southwest Saudi Arabia with some biological information, world-wide geographical distribution and taxonomic features. Saudi Journal of Biological Science 13 (1), 182 - 192." type="journal article" year="2006">Dawah &amp; Abdullah (2006)</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="El-Hawagry, M. S. &amp; Abdel-Dayem, M. S. &amp; Al Dhafer, H. M." pageId="51" pageNumber="52" pagination="1377 - 1393" refId="ref28395" refString="El-Hawagry, M. S., Abdel-Dayem, M. S. &amp; Al Dhafer, H. M. (2018) A contribution to the knowledge of fly fauna in the Kingdom of Saudi Arabia: new country records and an account of flies identified from Rawdhats, Riyadh Region, with biogeographical remarks (Insecta: Diptera). Journal of Natural History, 52 (21 - 22), 1377 - 1393." type="journal article" year="2018">
El-Hawagry 
<emphasis box="[227,283,538,564]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">et al.</emphasis>
(2018)
</bibRefCitation>
. It was described from 
<collectingCountry box="[624,691,539,565]" name="Egypt" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Egypt</collectingCountry>
and further recorded from 
<collectingCountry box="[991,1092,538,564]" name="Palestine" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Palestine</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[1145,1240,538,564]" name="Pakistan" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Pakistan</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Nartshuk, E. P." box="[1253,1424,538,565]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" pagination="222 - 299" refId="ref29369" refString="Nartshuk, E. P. (1984) Family Chloropidae. In: Soos A, Papp, L. (editors) Catalogue of Palaearctic Diptera, Volume 10, pp. 222 - 299. Elsevier, Budapest. 402 pp." type="book chapter" year="1984">Nartshuk 1984</bibRefCitation>
). It is further recorded from 
<collectingCountry box="[448,519,574,600]" name="Oman" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Oman</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[523,610,574,600]" name="Tunisia" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Tunisia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[620,678,574,600]" name="United Arab Emirates" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">UAE</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[731,809,574,600]" name="Yemen" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Yemen</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Deeming, J. C." box="[823,994,574,600]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" pagination="784 - 806" refId="ref27916" refString="Deeming, J. C. (2011) Order Diptera, family Chloropidae. In: van Harten A, editors. Arthropod Fauna of the United Arab Emirates, Volume 4, pp. 784 - 806. Dar Al-Ummah Printing, Publishing, Distribution and Advertising, Abu Dhabi, UAE. 816 pp." type="book chapter" year="2011">Deeming 2011</bibRefCitation>
). There are some specimens of this species in NMWC collected from 
<collectingCountry box="[497,558,610,636]" name="India" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">India</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
